Language models including BERT are trained to fit the predictability of tokens in strings. Therefore, the learned representation is not going to have the expected properties of numbers. After all, this is not a simple task if you consider different units, packages and etc which can affect how we should evaluate numbers. I recommend this paper for more discussion and research on this topic: 

&gt; Spithourakis, G., &amp; Riedel, S. (2018, July). Numeracy for Language Models: Evaluating and Improving their Ability to Predict Numbers. In Proceedings of the 56th Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics (Volume 1: Long Papers) (pp. 2104-2115).
